subSubSection.paragraph:
Description of 
holotype
.

FEMALE. Length excluding ovipositor sheath 
4.9 mm
. Head with greenish-blue metallic luster, upper face more blue, vertex purple (
Figs 23, 25
); setae of face, gena and occiput white, parascrobal region with two rows of white setae (
Fig. 23
), setae of vertex dark brown (
Figs 23, 25
). Maxillary and labial palpi dark brown to black (
Figs 23, 24
). Antennal scape black with greenish-purple metallic luster, pedicel and flagellum dark brown, tip of clava light brown (
Fig. 24
). Pronotum with coppery, purple and green metallic luster, setae dark brown to black (
Fig. 22
); mesoscutum with greenish-blue metallic luster, and with white hair-like setae (
Fig. 22
); prepectus with frontal surface dark brown with metallic purple luster, lateral surface brown (
Fig. 21
); tegula dark brown with brown setae(
Fig. 22
); mesopectus bluish green, with long white setae linearly arranged along acropleural sulcus; acropleuron black with dark purple metallic luster (
Fig. 21
); scutellar-axillar complex black with greenish-blue metallic luster, setae dark brown (
Fig. 22
). Fore wing (
Fig. 28
) infuscate beyond level of parastigma and gradually lightened distally, but with hyaline spot encompassing apex of marginal vein and base of stigmal vein with white setae (
Fig. 26
). Legs with knee yellowish brown, femora and tibiae dark brown (
Fig. 21
); basal half of dorsal margin of metatibia light brown to yellowish white (
Figs 21, 29
), metatibia with white hair-like setae; protarsus brown, mesotarsus pale yellowish brown except rows of pegs and spur brown; metatarsus yellowish brown (
Figs 21, 29
). Metanotum and propodeum dark brown with greenish-blue metallic luster; propodeum with a patch of white hair-like setae mesad to spiracle and callar region setose lateral to spiracle (
Fig. 27
). Gaster elongate-lanceolate, brown with metallic luster (
Fig. 28
); apex of syntergum dark brown, ovipositor sheath dark brown with apex brown (
Fig. 28
).

Head in frontal view (
Fig. 23
) 1.22× wider than high; in dorsal view (
Fig. 25
) width 1.63× length, with interocular distance 0.17× head width and less than width of eye; in lateral view (
Fig. 24
) with face convex, 1.40× higher than long. Eye height 1.0× eye width in lateral view (
Fig. 24
); distance between eyes below 4.67× distance between eyes above (
Fig. 23
); malar space 0.49× eye height (
Fig. 24
); distance between toruli greater than distance between torulus and clypeal margin, and greater than distance between torulus and orbit. OOL: POL: LOL: MPOD = 1: 3.7: 6.5: 4.5. Vertex coriaceous around ocelli and imbricate posteriorly (
Fig. 25
); lower face finely reticulaterugose (
Fig. 23
); gena longitudinally reticulate (
Fig. 24
); parascrobal region narrow; scrobal depression reticulate and transversely imbricate; interantennal region transversely reticulate (
Fig. 23
). Scrobal depression deep, separated from anterior ocellus by distance equal to diameter of anterior ocellus. Lower orbit above level of ventral margin of torulus. Antenna with scape normal, not expanded (
Fig. 24
); relative length (width) of scape = 40(8); pedicel 13(5); 1 
st
to 8 
th
funiculars: 4(5), 16(6), 18(7), 15(9), 12(10), 9(11), 8(12), 7.5(12); clava 23(13).

Pronotum in dorsal view divided medially, subtriangular, reticulate (
Fig. 22
). Mesoscutum almost flat but slightly convex anteriorly, lateral lobe carinate posteriorly (
Fig. 22
). Scutellar-axillar complex flat, longitudinally, coarsely reticulate, with dark brown setae; scutellum 1.32× longer than broad (
Fig. 22
). Mesopectus meshlike reticulate, acropleuron with very fine longitudinally aligned coriaceous sculpture (
Fig. 21
). Fore wing extended near apex of gaster, with SMV: MV: PMV: STV = 25: 29: 16: 9. Mesotibial spur shorter than basitarsus; mesotarsus with row of pegs on either side of basal four tarsomeres (
Fig. 21
). Hind leg with basitarsus as long as following two tarsomeres combined (
Fig. 29
). Propodeum with anterior margin broadly U-shaped (
Figs 27
, 
46
, indicated by arrows); plical region narrow, reticulate; callar region smooth and shiny (
Figs 27
, 
46
).
